 Russian Ark (2002) and Godard's Notre Musique (2004), Ravetto-Biagioli demonstrates the ways in which these filmmakers engage and evaluate the recent reconceptualization of Europe's borders, mythic figures, and identity paradoxes. Her work not only analyzes how these filmmakers thematically treat the idea of Europe but also how their work questions the ability of the moving image to challenge conventional ways of understanding history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszEuropexHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311054330808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2017z9783110547726oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/rave1821840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231544108423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231544108.jpg  a978-3-11-054330-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPKb2017